This paper deals with the problem of indoor positioning and navigation using deep convolutional neural networks. The paper focuses on computer vision techniques such as photogrammetry and CNNs, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) research. The paper also involves training deep neural networks (cs.AI) and optimizing their performance (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the application of these techniques to image processing (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
